        <h2>Talks and Presentations</h2>

        <p>Over the past 30 years, as an industry scientist, educator, and academic, Dr. Lavian has co-authored and presented numerous publications, journal articles, and peer-reviewed papers at conferences and scientific workshops. I&rsquo;ve included the presentation slides below.</p>

        <p>As an expert in network communications, Dr. Lavian has presented essential innovations in the digital age, including telecommunications, data communications, network architecture, broadband, Internet Protocols, voice, and video streaming. His papers are widely cited within the technology industry, academia, and the community.</p>

        <h2>Presentations in the areas of:</h2>

        <ul>
          <li>Network protocols and software applications&mdash;including the data link, network, and transport layers (L2, L3, L4) plus data center network architecture</li>
          <li>LANs, WANs, VPNs, and routing protocols&mdash;from RIP, BGP, MPLS, and OSPF to multicast, DNS, QoS, switching, and packet switching</li>
          <li>PSTN as well as IP telephony, VoIP, SIP, RTP, SS7</li>
          <li>Streaming media, SMS and instant messaging/chat via video and audio</li>
          <li>Wi-Fi and 802.11 Standards</li>
          <li>Wireless LAN (WLAN)</li>
          <li>TCP/IP Suite, TCP, UDP, and IP</li>
          <li>Ethernet and IEEE 802.3 Standard</li>
          <li>IETF RFC standards</li>
        </ul>

